Error: A Common Minecraft Error That Beginners Encounter Is A "Java.Lang.OutOfMemoryError" Error. This Error Occurs When Minecraft Does Not Have Enough Memory Allocated To It To Run Properly.

Step-By-Step

Solution: 1. Firstly, close Minecraft and any other applications that are running on your computer. 

2. Open your Minecraft launcher and click on "Installations" in the top menu bar. 

3. Select the installation that you are trying to play and click on the "Edit" button on
